11
Tutor Tier Update
Since the last time I created this Pokedex, the 
Attacks have changed a lot and as such, the 
Tutor Lists for each Pokemon have a lot of 
innaccuracies. This update will review and 
rectify them. 
Legendary + Mythical Addition
There are numerous ways of running Mythical 
Pokemon and Legendary Pokemon. This will be 
addressed in the Path of the Divine Module, in 
which Legends and Mythicals will be given various 
levels of importance and corresponding combat 
mechanics to be that appropriate threat level. This 
can cover Baby Legends that power up alongside 
trainers, standard legends that are just rare 
Pokemon and are slightly stronger, lower pantheon 
deific entities that are harder to deal with and 
greater deities that serve as end of campaign 
content that are massive threats.
Playtest Feedback
Most abilities were granted via flavor. Attack pools 
can be updated to make some abilities more viable 
to ability lists can change on wider feedback.
Dex Roadmap
Pokedex Entries
It is my belief that Pokedex entries grant a lot of 
fluff to Pokemon that GMs may not know otherwise, 
such as Audino having a highly advanced sense 
of hearing. All Pokemon will be given a dex entry 
at some point to allow GMs to grant more life to 
Pokemon. May update capabilities as well. We’ll have 
to cross reference World of Pokemon probably.
Dex Formatting & Polishing
I’m not 100% content with the design of the Pokedex 
and think it could be polished and reformatted to 
be more readable, concise and professional. For 
now it’ll do but i focused more on laying out the 
1000+ pages rather than making it look good. Made 
mistakes and didn’t use Character Styles. 
Fine Tuning
Some things like Levels at which Pokemon evolve 
may need some slight adjustments to account for 
campaign pacing. I also feel like making more niche 
Capabilities down the line. Maybe Sudowoodo will be 
hydrophobic and unable to swim.
The following updates will occur alongside the development of the PTE System in no particular order.  
Artist: Unknown

Dex Entry
Evolution Path
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Tutor Attack list is a combination of a Pokemon’s Egg Moves, TM 
List, and Tutor Moves in game. Each Attack is combined into a 
singular list and given a Tier Level. Tier 1 Can be learned at any 
Point. Tier 2 Requires them to be at least Level 20. 
Tier 3 Requires them to be at least Level 40.
Base Stats are the 
default Stats a 
Pokemon has
Their Evolution Path states what Pokemon they evolve into at what Levels
At Level 1, Pokemon always start with their 4 Starting Attacks
Whenever a Pokemon levels up, if their Level reaches a listed 
number above, they learn that Attack or may replace an Attack on 
their Attack List with the listed Attack if they desire.
This shows a Picture of the default species!
Basic Info contains 
their type combo and 
the Abilities they can 
possibly
Capabilities are the 
innate qualities of the 
Pokemon, separated 
into Movement, 
Combat and Narrative 
effects.
Skill Information contains 
the Species Skill Ranks of this 
Pokemon. See Pokemon Skills 
for info.
Other Information will 
contain minor information 
about the Pokemon such as 
their Size, Weight and Diet.
The Dex entry contains a small paragraph that describes the Pokemon 
and basic info about them.
12
Reading a Dex Entry
As Bulbasaur evolves it gains strength in its hind legs, being able to support a much larger bulb. When night comes and its bulb is no 
longer absorbing energy, some of the energy is expended as a sweet aroma, however this only occurs when Ivysaur is sleeping. The 
expendature of this energy is primarily used for healing Ivysaur, with the aroma being a byproduct similar to how humans sweat.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Bulbasaur are born with large seeds that bloom upon birth upon their back. While they can choose to be a herbivore, most Bulbasaur 
gain nutrients from absorbing sunlight through these bulbs. Energy gained through their bulb can be stored as residual power in case 
Bulbasaur needs it, however most store energy in order to evolve sooner. 
Bulbasaur (Base) > Ivysaur (15) > Venusaur (30)

Ivysaur

============================================================
PAGE 15

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Upon evolution, Venusaur has its bulb bloom into a large trunked flower. The color of this flower often depends on the terrain bulbasaur 
grew up in and how much sunlight it absorbed during its youth. Moderate sunlight areas usually result in Red Flowers while areas of 
harsh sunlight like deserts lead to Orange Flowers. If raised without sunlight in a cave, the Flower is Gray and smaller in stature. 
Bulbasaur (Base) > Ivysaur (15) > Venusaur (30)

Evolution Path
The leaf on Chikorita’s head is used as an indicator of temperature and humidity. The leaf will often point towards directions of higher 
humidity, similar to a compass. Chikorita enjoy these types of areas so they’re often found sunbathing near Grasslands or shores. 
Chikorita are extremely docile as a species, always straying away from battle unless their convictions force them to battle. 
Chikorita (Base) > Bayleef (15) > Meganium (30)

Evolution Path
On a Bayleef’s neck are multiple curled up leaves, each one containing a tree shoot. Many pheromones are secreted from these leaves, 
leading to multiple effects on people around them. Sometimes spicy aroma can come out, having curative properties. Sometimes a 
bitter aroma comes out, leading to others becoming excited. Sometimes a foul aroma comes out, inducing rage in those who smell it.

Base Stats
Evolution Path
As the leaves on Bayleef turn into the large flower on a Meganium, its aroma coelesces into a pleasant smelling substance. As 
Meganium absorbs sunlight, the flower will increase in saturation. Using the absorbed power, Meganium can breath a gale of 
chemicals. These chemicals promote growth in plants, enough to even reverse the process of death in plantlife.

When a Treecko evolves into a Grovyle, it becomes confident in its strength to protect others. Instead of sticking with Pokemon,

The leaves on Sceptile’s body, primarily its arms are literal blades and nearly as sharp as steel. Unlike Grovyle, Sceptile prefer to wander

Evolution Path
The shell on turtwig’s back is actually made out of soil and clay. Whenever a Turtwig is dehydrated, its leaf will wilt and the shell on its 
back becomes dry and brittle. This leads Turtwigs to usually find a home somewhere near forest lakes and ponds for quick access to 
water. On a whim, Turtwig can use the water in its shell to harden and deflect physical attacks, becoming much sturdier for combat.

Evolution Path
When a Torterra is fully mature, soil begins to encompass its entire shell, being able to sustain plantlife and grow massive trees. Even 
the Trees themselves normally sprout berries at some point. When dusk occurs, Torterras normally burrow halfway underground for 
camouflage and to absorb soil nutrients. Many small Pokemon such as pikipek live their entire lives on the back of a Torterra.

Evolution Path
Snivy often excels at using its wits to maneuver around enemies within battle, transforming chlorophyll into energy that can make it 
swifter. Considering the hands and feet of a Snivy are often short and flimsy, it uses its snake like body to maneuver quicker in combat

The regal stare of a Serperior is enough to often stop an opponent in their steps. The energy from Photosynthesis is often used either

Dartrix tend to gain a massive ego to the point of narcicism, especially to the point of cleanliness. It will always keep its wings preened

The stick on the head of a Grookey seems to always be hollowed out. Whenever they hit the stick against the ground, a sound

Coiled around the collar of a Floragato is a long vine that is attached to a flower bud. Floragato will often use this flower chain as

Evolution Path
The flame at the tip of its tail is an indication of Charmander’s Life Force and Emotional state. If Charmander or its evolutions have a 
fiercly active tail, it is likely enraged, wary or excited. If the flame is weak, it is likely saddened or weak. While water can make the flame 
weaker, being submerged risks it extinguishing and puts Charmander’s life in danger. It tends to bite and claw more than using fire.

Evolution Path
Whenever Braixen evolves, it finds the sturdiest branch within its forest and keeps it in its tail to use as a weapon. When pulling the twig 
from its tail, the friction from the heated fur ignites it, which it can manipulate to use in battle and amplify its psychic powers that are 
budding at this stage. Braixen often command other pokemon that are under its care using the enflamed twig.

Evolution Path
The bell-like object attached at the base of Torracat’s neck is a flame sac, an organ that can produce flames that appear when evolving. 
Torracat’s emotions cause a rise in the organ’s temperature, and when the organ spits flames, it rings with the high, clear sound of a bell. 
Torracat attacks using the flames emitted from this bell. Torracat are often rebellious and its defiance makes it easier to charge power.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path (Split Evolution)
You can tell the origins of a Dewott based on the way it uses its scalchops. Wild and untrained Dewott tend to be more reckless when 
using the shell to slash at enemies, leaving many weak points and room for counter attacks. A disciplined or trained Dewott tends to be 
defensive in nature and uses its dual weapons to counter attack, taking advantage of weak spots in their opponent’s stances.

Evolution Path
The scalchops of dewott eventually turn into shell-like armor that braces the limbs and helm of a Samurott. Instead of a scalchop, it gains 
a seamitar attached to its anterior legs, which it can wield and sheathe at will, surprising enemies. When swimming, the horn on the helm 
of Samurott tends to create a vortex of water as it speeds by like a bullet, leaving behind massive ripples and waves as it passes.

When evolving into a Frogadier, they become much mor versatile with their bubble creation, allowing them to obscure the vision of 
others and learning more offensive uses. As a Frogadier runs, they can launch bubbles behind them to both increase their speed and 
distract potential pursuers. Much like most amphibian Pokemon, the mucus lining their hands allow them to stick to walls with ease.

Evolution Path
Instead of bubbles, Greninja learns upon evolving to compact them into star shapes, similar to a shuriken. These stars of compressed 
water can be thrown at high enough speeds to split metal in two and slice through even the hardest of stones. The combat style of a 
Ninja, along with their weapon usage was said to be heavily inspired by Greninja and how they train.

Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Popplio create special bouncy balloons to send at its opponents. When the balloons pop, the sheer force of their bursting is what deals 
damage. Bubbles are formed this way through bodily fluids expelled from their nose and with enough focus and training, they can 
create bubbles nearly twice its size. Popplio tend to be very social Pokemon, enjoying the attention from others.

Evolution Path
Brionne has a deep compassion for its friends or Trainer. Whenever they feel down it performs or enacts a cheery dance to try and help. 
Compared to when it was a Popplio, Brionne enjoys dancing and singing, often learning the tunes of other Pokemon until it can mimic 
it. It gets excited when it sees a dance it doesn’t know. This hard worker practices diligently until it can learn that dance.

As it dances, Primarina releases balloons of water into the area around itself, moving them using the sound waves from its voice. The 
sight of moonlight reflecting off its glittering balloons creates a magical scene. Its greatest enemies are arid environments and the

When scared, this Pokémon cries as a defense mechanism. Its tears have a chemical composition similar to onions, and attackers 
won’t be able to resist weeping by proxy. When it gets wet, its skin changes color, and this Pokémon becomes invisible as if it were 
camouflaged. Often times when scared it jumps into the nearest lake to obscure itself and hide its shame.

Evolution Path
Drizzile tend to be very non-confrontational Pokemon, preferring silence and being left alone. Whenever a Drizzile has a permanent 
home or den, it tends to lay traps outside in order to keep strangers out of its territory. The phrase “you’re being a drizz” or anything 
similar comes from the fact that Drizzile are often highly intelligent but choose to not apply themselves, by being lazy or otherwise.

Evolution Path
Quaxly are only found within lakes that are free of polution and are in pristine condition due to their tidy nature. The feathers on their body 
tends to reflect the nature of their environment, if they’re clean and white, they live in pure water. If the feathers are gray or rough, they live 
in rougher water or the ocean. When absorbing clean water, its feathers secrete a gel that keep itself clean and deflect dirt from sticking.

Dustox are known to have highly sensitive bodies that are prone to changes in temperature. As such, they tend to be nocturnal and 
hide from sunlight. Dustox are often found towards very small sources of heat such as bonfires or street lamps which they use to warm

Evolution Path
The primary diet of Scatterbug tend to be poisonous leaves and polluted trash, as they don’t have to compete for it. A byproduct of 
converting toxic substances to nutrients involves creating a small surplus of black powder. This powder is secreted through their skin 
which regulates temperature, allowing them to live in many climates. On contact it also tends to paralyze their predators.

Evolution Path
The first Vikavolt to evolve in a colony of dormant Charjabug often steal one of them and fly away. This Charjabug is held as a second

Kingambit that controls a region and serves as a king to every Pawniard within miles, often forming its own dominion to rule. The

Dratini are often born larger than Dratini, however over their childhood they repeatedly shed their skin and get longer in the process 
of becoming a Dragonair. If the Dratini is in a rapid body of water if often sheds less to stay protected, resulting in a smaller evolution.

============================================================
PAGE 155
============================================================
Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
The dorsal fin on Frigibax absorbs heat from around it and converts it to cold energy within its stomach. This allows Frigibax to live in 
nearly any climate, however it still prefers Tundras as it takes less energy to build nests compared to other Terrains. There are some 
cases of Frigibaxs living in volcanic tunnels, converting the heat in order to create mini refridgerated cavern nests. 
Frigibax (Base) > Arctibax (20) > Baxcalibur (40)

============================================================
PAGE 156

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Arctibax are often terrifyingly aggressive predators wherever they may live. As they evolve, they gain masks of frozen ice, formed from 
the ability to freeze air around them simply with their breath. Their dorsal fins also change and gain the ability to use stored energy to 
form sheets of sharp ice around the fin, using it to slash through enemies as if it were sharp as a blade. 
Frigibax (Base) > Arctibax (20) > Baxcalibur (40)

============================================================
PAGE 157
============================================================
Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Baxcalibur are the only known Ice Pokemon that can live comfortably in Volcanos, using the super heated air to empower itself even 
stronger than it would be in Tundras. When coming across the frozen den of a Baxcalibur, beware as it can blast cryogenic air towards 
its enemies with the strength to instantly inflict frostbite. Its breath is strong enough to even freeze liquid lava in the matter of a minute.
Frigibax (Base) > Arctibax (20) > Baxcalibur (40)

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Pawmi’s Electric Sacs on its cheeks are barely functional when its first born until suitably trained. Electricity can only be produced if it 
furiously rubs its cheeks with enough friction but even then it barely has enough power to match a Pichu. When it creates static through 
rubbing its cheeks, it will often stand on its hind legs and throw thunder strikes at its enemies, though it often misses.

Pawmi

============================================================
PAGE 178

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
As Pawmi evolves, its Electric Sac becomes more developed and it gains the ability to use its paw pads as a conduit for electricity 
generated by them. It often gains a lot of confidence and defends herds of Pokemon it travels with by leaping at enemies and hitting 
them with a flurry of hits. Once Pawmo gets heated it will often expend all its electricity in a flurry of strikes, exhausting it in the process.
Pawmi (Base) > Pawmo (10) > Pawmot (30)

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Pawmot are often gentle and kind creatures and take a while to understand combatative intent, however once they get fired up, they 
become lightning fast. The fur on Pawmot’s body can store an immense amount of electricity that surpasses any battery that has been 
able to be created industrially to our knowledge and is often kept as pets in power plants to assist in energy generation.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Tinkatink and its evolutions are incredibly versatile at using scrap material to make weapons to defend itself. Though in this stage it can 
only wield smaller items such as clubs or mallets which it uses to bully other Pokemon into performing its bidding. Researchers suggest 
this behavior is simply a cry for attention due to its poor ability to socialize, however most think it’s just rude.
Tinkatink (Base) > Tinkatuff (20) > Tinkaton (40)

If Tinkatuff has a social group that performs its bidding, it will order them to gather scrap each day, which is used to craft a larger or 
stronger weapon for itself. Though it often uses this weapon to defend its servants rather than simply bullying others. Smaller Pokemon

Evolution Path
Wild Tinkaton often take at least 1 Year to gather enough scrap to form the massive weapons they’re known for, though this process is 
sped up if they live ina city or quarry. Most Tinkaton tend to have daring and mischevious dispositions and use their weapon to torment 
other Pokemon. The Pokemon it targets, however, are nearly always stronger than itself, or they tend to be avian Pokemon species.

It is said that once you die and reach Final Judgment, you may choose to wander Phemenon instead of going to the Aether if you were 
a good person. Those that are often filled with regret choose this to continue living a new life or to watch over their loved ones. Often

Evolution Path
A very popular theory in the paranormal field is that Duskull are the physical manifestations of souls. Souls that have no purpose but are 
disconnected from their bodies somehow will take on the form of a duskull and wander endlessly pursuing meaning. The light behind 
the mask of a Duskull is said to be a soul, its color changing depending on the mood of Duskull, similar to Aura. 
Duskull (Base) > Dusclops (25) > Dusknoir (40)

Dex Entry

Evolution Path
Rumors of Litwick began when an envious Gastly possessed a wick candle within a castle. After possessing the candle, its flame glows 
bright purple, the brighter it is the happier the Litwick is. However over time it will start to melt and die out, causing the realization it 
possessed an ephemeral form. To combat this, it absorbs a small amount of life force from people nearby, restoring its vitality.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Gimmighoul are small creatures that enjoy stealing riches from areas around them and bringing them back to their hideouts. They 
serve no other purpose than to gain the most wealth possible and avoid conflict to while doing so, by any means. Special breeds of 
Houndour have been bred in Gabyrgg due to the notoriety of theives using Gimmighoul to steal from vendors without being noticed.

============================================================
PAGE 217
============================================================
Dex Entry
Base Stats
Most of the time, Gimmighoul will store treasures it steals in small coves or bushes, however sometimes they will find a chest or storage 
container. It will then claim that chest and enter its chest form. Once it gathers enough wealth, Gimmighoul will be content and evolve 
into into this new form and will not leave to gather more. Anyone who touches its chest will have energy drained from them.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Smoliv often protect itself from predators by emitting oil from the fruit on its head. This oil is extremely bitter and its aroma alone is 
enough to make someone flinch. Many avian Pokemon tend to avoid Smoliv as a result of this so they’re often kept close to other Grass 
Pokemon in colonies to protect them by proxy. Fortunately Grass Pokemon don’t mind the aroma as much.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
When Smoliv evolves, the oil created from its fruit becomes pleasant and contains a scent of freshness compared to its previous 
bitterness. As such, during this stage, Dolliv are very fragile and must be protected by its friends to not be preyed upon by those 
allured by it. The more a Dolliv sunbathes, the more pleasant its fruit will become and it often results in a quicker evolution.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Most gardens have at least one Arboliva who is revered by most Pokemon native to the area. Using the rich soil to derive nutrients 
from, Arboliva grows fruit that is capable of healing even the deadliest of wounds, and is happy to do so. To those that threaten it, 
Arboliva tend to launch globs of aromatic oil at them with enough force to smash a boulder. 
Smoliv (Base) > Dolliv (20) > Arboliva (30)

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Due to the poor eyesight of Swinub they often rely on other senses to interact with the world. Their sense of smell is very acute, being 
about to find berries and mushrooms even in the arctic north of Kostrya. They also are very sensitive to seismic action. Whenever 
villagers see the Swinub acting crazy or nervous, it is an indicator of either an incoming avalanche or swarm of Pokemon approaching.
Swinub (Base) > Piloswine (20) > Mamoswine (30)

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Upon evolution, Chansey gains the ability to create highly nutrious eggs at least once per week. It often derrives joy from sharing its 
eggs to its friends as a source of food. While other Pokemon are very protective of their eggs, Chansey doesn’t seem to mind for some 
odd reason. Its eggs are often a high source of vitamins and nutrients, leading it to be used in hospitals for supplements to the sick. 
Happiny (Base) > Chansey (20) > Blissey (30)

Evolution Path
The older a Chansey and Blissey get, the more nutrious their eggs become, even being high enough in dopamine to make the 
consumer happy as a result. However after a certain point Blissey creates fewer and fewer eggs, leading to its loss in value. It then 
focuses on caring for the eggs of other Pokemon, storing them in its heated pouch and caring for it as if it was its own child.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Nacli were born in the deepest layer of the crust of the world with their bodies made of pure rock salt. As they grow or move, their 
bodies scrape against objects and leave salt behind, thus making it a valuable ally for early settlers that wished to preserve food. If a 
Nacli becomes injured their body will crack, leaving it defenseless and crumbling. 
Nacli (Base) > Naclstack (20) > Garganacl (40)

The salt created by Naclstack is incredibly strong and used for dry curing its enemies. Having any salt sprayed on its victims will absorb 
the water from their body through their skin and can lead to rapid dehydration. Not only that but when charging an attack, Naclstack 
will often spray hardened salt pellets at its enemies that are fast enough to pierce through iron.

Evolution Path
Garganacl has the ability to control the aspects of the salt it creates depending on what it consumes. Some salt it creates has healing 
factors that when sprinkled over wounds, immeidately cauterizes and heals. Some salt are as hard as bullets and can induce burning on its 
enemies. Some salt enhances the taste of food even more than normal salt. Garganacl however prefers to live in caves away from humans.

Evolution Path
Within the first few days of birth, Aron instinctively searches for iron to consume and forge into the steel that coats its body, each time 
they evolve they shed off this armor and use inner reserves to become bigger. Aron were essential with early nations as they served as a

The territorial nature of an Aggron tends to dominate sections of the mountains they’re home to, even becoming problems for many

Evolution Path
Sometimes the spirits of warriors will cease to leave the Mortal Plane, clinging to the fight that was their last moment. They will 
immediately possess a weapon and a Honedge will be created, stuck in this form with only the memories of conflict remaining as their 
families become a distant shroud. It will intertwine its blue sash around Trainer’s arms to assist it in battle, sharing its memories as well.

============================================================
PAGE 363
============================================================
Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
With the usage of a Protector, Scyther is able to harden its body, taking stones around it and forming it into a rocky exoskeleton. 
Instead of scythes it instead gains a stone axe on each appendage which it uses as a makeshift shield and weapon. Despite its dull 
appearance however these axes are increadibly sharp, being able to fell trees, however they dull as Kleavor ages. 
Scyther (Base) > Scizor (30)

Kricketot

============================================================
PAGE 378
============================================================
Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Using its knife-like arms it can scrape against each other to create melodious tunes. Conversely it can also scrape against each other 
to create shrill sounding noise that is painful to listen to. By creating music it can either lure Pokemon near it with harmonious tunes or 
drive them away with sharp screeches. The older a Kricketune, the more dull this tune becomes over time.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Over time, Tarountula have developed silk threads that are elastic and tough enough to deflect the scythes of a Scyther, who used to be 
a prime predator of this Pokemon. At night time, Tarountula often retreats into its ball of silk and hangs from a tree. Even the deadliest 
of attacks are minimized while in this cocoon state. The silk created by Tarountula is often used for military grade fabric. 
Tarountula (Base) > Spidops (15)

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
The territory of a Spidops is often deadlier than any other arachnid Pokemon such as Ariados. Within the claimed territory of a Spidops, 
they will set many traps in order to deter outsiders which include webs of thread. This thread maintains the sturdiness of its former 
stage, however it also gains a residue that coats it and makes the thread extremely sticky and traps smaller Pokemon in their tracks.

Evolution Path
Nymbles gain their name from how nimble they are in combat, often unable to be hit unless their enemies are extremely precise or 
focused. It will often bounce around in combat, using the force from jumping to hurt enemies by ramming into them. Using the second 
set of legs on its back, they can detract and function as a spring, launching Nymble up to 30 Feet in the air.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
When evolving, Lokix’s second set of legs gain spiked appendages which can be controled like a chainsaw. It doesn’t use these legs for 
jumping since it is stronger now, however it uses them primarily for combat and performing deadlier kicks. These legs can still be used 
as normal however and is most useful to run up walls as the spikes snag onto the rough surface and allow it to surf on walls.

Evolution Path
Rellor will endlessly spend days within the desert rolling up sand and mud in order to create a small mudball. This mudball is slowly 
imbued with the energy of Rellor as time progresses, becoming a mixture of dirt, sand, mud and psionic aura. Rellor will continue to 
slowly grow the mudball bigger until it either dies or evolves once enough energy has been fed to the mudball. 
Rellor (Base) > Rabsca (25)

Once the mudball gains enough energy it will transform into a pure ball of psychic energy and Rellor will become paralyzed and 
unable to move. Its scarab form will become stiff and lifeless while the psychic ball floats around and performs most of the attacking.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Maschiff are often the most aggressive and loveable canine Pokemon that is known to date. When Maschiff develops trust with its social 
group, it will defend them to the death and distrust anyone outside of its group. Unless provoked, wild Maschiff are often all bark and no 
bite and will only defend its friends. Maschiff will only get serious when it encounters a threat stronger than it or its allies are threatened.

Mabosstiff can store energy in its large dewlap, unleashing this energy all at once to blow away enemies for a large force of strength 
to deter enemies. Mabosstiff is deemed one of the most selfless Pokemon, risking death to defend its family and those it cares for,

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Tadbulb often gather energy from the plasma in the air around them, using their energy reserves to float around away from the 
predators on the ground. During thunderstorms they often float near the cloudline, gathering energy from lightning around them. 
Whenever Tadbulb senses danger it will blink the light in its head to alert its allies which is often useful for watchtowers and towns.

============================================================

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Be wary of the false eyes on the side of a Bellibolt’s head, as they are actually organs for discharging electricity. Whenever the blubbery 
belly of Bellibolt is hit with an attack, the kinetic energy is absorbed and converted into electricity which it can use to strike back. Often 
times when a Bellibolt is about to fight, it will slap its stomach rapidly and as it drums, energy will start to accumulate in its gut.

An ancient fable in Aethia describes the origins of Milcery. A famous bakery in Esgate created delicious pasteries but had a no 
Pokemon policy. One gastly decided to challenge this by possessing a vat of cream, forming a new body where it could eat all it wanted 
without suspicion. How Milcery bred beyond that is unknown. Milcery evolves based on the food it eats and the type of flavors it enjoys.

Evolution Path
Alcremie are almost never the same visually, their creamy bodies differing depending on their diet when they were a Milcery. 
Depending on how happy Alcremie is or how it was treated when it was young, the cream in its body will become sweeter. Though 
conversely, if an Alcremie is treated poorly, the cream will become much more toxic and inedible, allowing it to be effective in battle.

The breath that Fidough had is now expanded to its aura and aroma as well, so anything that grows near Dachsbun is assisted by its

============================================================
PAGE 454

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Mankey tend to have a very prideful personality, so sometimes when they would lose in battle, a mental switch is triggered and it gains 
control of its anger. Some may even say that through fainting, Mankey reaches an enlightenment to control its rage as it evolves into an 
Annihilape instead of a Primeape. Annihilape can remain calm when enraged, but channel its anger into deadly and accurate blows.
Mankey (Base) > Primeape (25)

Evolution Path
It is rumored that Charcadets are born when charcoal is imbued with life energy and becomes a Pokemon. The energy of Charcadet is 
nearly unmatchable, so much so that they rarely ever get tired and spend almost every waking moment in combat, sparring or training. 
Depending on the vlaues of Charcadet and the way it experiences its childhood, it will evolve to different forms.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
In normal cases, Charcadet will often evolve into Armarouge. This Pokemon keeps the vital spirit of its prior form and use its expert 
skills in combat to enact its own form of Justice. Armarouge will never turn down a fight against evildoers and will always interefere if 
someone needs help, even if its allies don’t assist them. The armor it gains has a built in cannon that can shoot out flames at enemies.
Charcadet (Base) > Armarouge (30)

Evolution Path
If a Charcadet loses faith in its own skills, is mistreated or is exposed to negative energy, it will instead evolve into Ceruledge. The 
Fiery Blades on its arms become fueled by its own resentment towards others or those who wronged it and it will enact its vengeance 
eternall until its satisfied. Through its own ways, Ceruledge still has a code of justice, however it becomes more of a Vigilante.

Evolution Path
Noibat are often found only in the deepest chasms and caves, wherever the light is dimmest. Their ultrasonic waves can be used for 
disorientation, sonar, and finding ripe fruit. They’re often a valuable companion for chefs due to this ability. As they release a sonic 
radar, they can tell how ripe a fruit is depending on the feedback they get from the fruit and how it reacts to the vibrations.

Evolution Path
Noiverns are well known as the “Wyvern of the Night”, due to their nocturnal predatory nature. They’re often cruel to their prey and 
can leave dents in the side of mountains with their sonic lances and ultrasonic waves. However Noivern can easily be tamed with those 
that provide it ripe and fresh fruit. They will often protect sources of food, even if they’re not formally trained.

When Wattrel flies, the wind that pushes against its wings generates electricity that is stored within their bones and channeled 
throughout their body. Wattrel are almost exclusively found on cliffs near beaches, as its favorite prey are fish Pokemon. Wattrel will

Dex Entry

Evolution Path
Kilowattrel are well known as one of the most durable avian Pokemon, able to fly for nearly 2 days without eating. In addition to storing 
energy in their bones as they fly through the airstreams, they also have a much larger throat sac which can store a larger reserve of 
electricity. Whenever threatened, Kilowattrel will often expend all the energy in its throat sac in a massive discharge to eliminate enemies.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Mismagius tends to feed on fear, absorbing any residual amounts within its ruby gem. If it has any fear residing in its gem it will recall on 
these memories and create visions based on the fear in order to terrify others. The curses derived from Mismagius range from terrifying 
visions to eternal dread to awful headaches to feelings of hopelessness. Its cries sound like incantations from a distance.

Dex Entry

Evolution Path
In a sad tale of irony, considering spirits are said to lose memories of their past lives, Shuppet never end up finding those they look 
for. The longer a Shuppet goes on the more its emotions start to influence its mental state. By the time it evolves into a Banette, the 
resentment and malice turns into a grudge. Banette spends its time searching for strangers to curse in place of its desired target. 
Shuppet (Base) > Banette (30)

============================================================

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
If a Drifloon decides to consume the LIfe Energy of those around it, its balloon will eventually expand into a hot air balloon until it 
evolves into Drifblim. While it is entirely capable of transporting people around, if often is carried by the wind, leading it to be a less 
reliable source of transportation. It can control its direction when flying however it expends stored Life Energy to do so. 
Drifloon (Base) > Drifblim (25)

Evolution Path
As a Yamask ages, its obsession with reforming its former life advances. It uses its mask to create a sarcophagus in which it attempts to 
reform its body inside. While normal people see the same mask and coffin between all Cofagrigus, each one has their delusions severe 
enough where they see their former body being reformed. Cofagrigus use Life Energy to reform it and are desparate to do so.

Evolution Path
It is fairly common for tall tales to be spread around the fire of small villages, these myths are useful for anthropology. One of these 
myths is the origin of Phantump. Legends say when a misbehaving child dies in the woods, their soul is blocked from going to the other 
side by the tall shrouds of the trees. Being trapped, it instead becomes one with the earth, possessing a stump to wander the forest.

Evolution Path
The longer a Phantump wanders the Forest the more resentful it becomes at the wandering trainers who have a life that it can no 
longer have. The fact it doesn’t have memories of its former life only enrages it further as it evolves into Trevenant. Most forests have a 
firm hierarchy of Trevenants who act as wardens, protecting the forest as if it was family. The eldest Trevenant is usually in charge.

Sometimes spirits return to the Mortal Plane in order to help others and be a benevolent force. These spirits take the form of a

wisdom, larger Pumpkaboo tend to be more calm and serene. During the night, they light up and follow travelers who are alone.

Evolution Path
Most Sandygast are quick to die from their own arrogance, however those that manage to evolve into Palossand gain an ego and let 
vanity control them. The apperance of their castle means everything to them and if someone tries to vandalize them, they will hunt even 
children to the end of the beach. Palossand are known as the antihesis of summer and are hunted mercilessly to keep the good vibes.

Evolution Path
Rumors say that Sinistea are formed when Gastly enter a home and possess kitchenware. Once possessed it will live in sollace, never 
interacting with the native family but being content with being around people to keep it company. If discovered it will attempt to flee 
desperately. Similar to the purple vapor of Gastly, Sinistea have a liquid form of the same poisonous gas, however it becomes its body.

Evolution Path
Sometimes Sinistea will get possessive of the home it inhabits rather than being a passive force. In order to show rebellion against the 
occupying family it will be mischevious, destroying some of the property in order to drive the family out. It is unknown whether this is 
genuine malice or a playful mischevious nature. It will often spit some of its poisonous liquid at enemies, smelling similar to tea.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Cottonee are a highly valuable commodity for any Fashionista due to the rapid rate of generating cotton by converting sunlight and 
any plant matter they consume. Whenever a Cottonee is threatened or embarassed it tends to launch cotton from its body to serve as a 
distraction. While not naturally formed in the wild, many cottonee are multicolored depending on the cotton needed by the seamstress.
Cottonee (Base) > Whimsicott (25)

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
While Whimsicott don’t require food outside of sunlight, they tend to visit settlements and cause havoc in residential homes. They sneak 
in through open windows, taking any shiny things they find and leave behind a trail of fluff at the scene of the crime. Whimsicott tend to 
be nomadic as they cannot control movement when it is windy, following the wind as it blows unless recalled. They don’t seem to mind.

Whenever Capsakid absorbs sunlight, the aroma that comes off of it becomes very spicy to even breathe in. The chemical conversion of 
energy is enough to even simulate burns with the same strength of fire. When the teeth of Capsakid shed, they are often used as spicy

Evolution Path
The organ that creates spicy chemicals is now isolated into the red head when it evolves into Scovillain and thus it is the only head that 
can control the fire-like chemicals. The green head often controls its Grass side but gets very irratated when the spicy chemicals are 
released, thus shifting its mood vastly. Scovillain can create a milder form of chemicals that can strengthen allies if they can handle it.

Dex Entry

Evolution Path
Whenever a soul wanders throughout the desert, they have a chance to get caught in the wind and tangled up with dry grass, 
becoming a Bramblin. Bramblin often have little control of where they move or control of their body itself so its movements are heavily 
dependant on the wind direction. If an enemy gets tangled in their branches, their life force will be slowly siphoned into itself. 
Bramblin (Base) > Brambleghast (30)

Dex Entry

Evolution Path
When Bramblin evolves, its body gains thorns and becomes much more cage like. When it runs into something its thorns will often get 
snagged into their body, preventing it from escaping as it encompasses them in a stranglehold. These thorns will remain lached onto 
their prey and siphon energy until there is none left or they faint. Once no energy is left, their thorns will release and it will move on.
Bramblin (Base) > Brambleghast (30)

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Baltoys were one of the few Pokemon originally made by human hands. It is said to have their origins in Ortheim where an old, long gone 
civilization tried to infuse inanimate objects with life. They bound soul fragments together, resulting in these clay puppets. Originally, 
they resembled a ruler after whose image they were made but after they were set free they lost that similarity, looking like they do today. 
Baltoy (Base) > Claydol (30)

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
The deep snow and icy tundras are no match for this Avalugg’s steel jaw, using it to cut through even the toughest of ice and even rock 
itself. It is said that this Avalugg was created as a result of over predation within the tundra, leading for it to adapt to traversal between 
the tundra and wastelands. When sleeping it often burrows into mountains, making small caves in the process. 
Bergmite (Base) > Avalugg (30)

Cetoddle

============================================================
PAGE 596
============================================================
Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Cetitan often wanders the snowy areas of its birth, warding off potential predators with its thick layer of muscles and fat, easily swatting 
aside even the roughest of dragons. Ice energy is built up within its lower jaw but can only be released through the conduits of its 
horns, releasing devastating icy beams. Its horns can reach cryogenic temperatures and can instantly freeze blood if they pierce you.
Cetoddle (Base) > Cetitan (30)

Ursaring

============================================================
PAGE 617
============================================================
Dex Entry
Base Stats
Evolution Path
Level-Up Attack List
Ursaluna is a fairly rare Pokemon, only being found in marshlands that are directly connected to forests that have native Teddiursa. Due 
to the playful nature of the Teddiursa it will end up playing near swamps and if desparate enough will scavenge for plantlife nearby. The 
exposure to such enviornment allows for it to evolve into Ursaluna who has a burlier body that can dig in these marshy terrains. 
Teddiursa (Base) > Ursaring (30)
Teddiursa (Base) > Ursaluna (30) 
Teddiursa (Base) > Ursaluna Blood Moon (30)

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
The tail of a Girafarig has a small brain of its own, oftentimes with a separate personality that tends to be more violent. This side of 
Girafarig tends to be focused solely on primal instincts and doesn’t sleep, so it protects Girafarig while it sleeps in exchange for food, 
as it can’t control motor functions of the legs. Try not to anger a Girafarig as the tail has little patience and a quick temper.

Dex Entry

Evolution Path
If Girafarig evolves, the tail merges with the main body and unites the two minds into a singular unit. The hardened scales of its tail now 
encase its body like a suit of armor, allowing it to become much more durable in battle. Farigiraf will often whip its head around, using 
the hardened portion of its skin to deal blunt force trauma to its enemies, often chasing them down until they are weakened.

Dex Entry

Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Dunsparce is a very average snake-like Pokemon that tends to avoid conflict. Using its drill shaped tail it can burrow into the ground 
and hide from predators for hours upon end. Wherever a Dunsparce live, many odd shaped, narrow tunnels are bound to be found as it 
can move backwards and propel itself with its tail. It has wings for some reason but they’re not strong enough to lift its body that much.

Evolution Path
Researchers are unaware if Dudunsparce is an actual Pokemon or a different form of Dunsparce. Most suggest that the more segments 
a Dunsparce has, the stronger it becomes. However others disagree and state that when a Dunsparce has 2 or 3 segments, it is 
considered an evolved form. The hotness and lack of consensus of this debate only show how average this Pokemon is.

Wyrdeer are only found within colder regions and said to be an adaptation of Stantler, forcing it to evolve when the circumstances 
demand it. Normally this would be classified as a Regional Variant, it is classified more as a Pokemon similar to Sawsbuck that adapt based 
on enviornmental factors. Unlike Stantler it seems their psionic potential is active and able to predict natural disasters similar to Absol.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Glameow tend to be a niche favorite for most feline enjoyers due to their fickleness but high affection. Whenever they’re displeased 
they tend to be cold to their Trainers but can forgive them if given enough attention. The movements of their tail tend to cause 
hypnosis which they use on strangers when begging for food in cities. Everstone pendants were invented because of Glameow. 
4 Bite - Dark
8 Swagger - Normal
12 Feint Attack - Dark
16 Fury Swipes - Normal
20 Assist - Normal
24 Captivate - Normal
28 Slash - Normal
32 Sucker Punch - Dark
36 Attract - Normal
40 Play Rough - Fairy
45 Hone Claws - Dark
50 Night Slash - Dark

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
If a Purugly is seen there are a few explanations. 1. It was wild and needed to fend for itself to survive. 2. Its owner is indiscriminate on 
the beauty of this Pokemon. 3. The Trainer is harvesting its shedded fur which is said to be as soft as velvet. Wild Purugly tend to be 
scornful towards others, especially when seeing other Glameow and younger Pokemon that taunt it for its lack of attention.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
The only thing that brings joy to the life of a Lechonk is finding food. It has an amazing sense of smell but refuses to use it for anything 
else other than foraging, even if it highly respects their trainer. The older a Lechonk gets, the more picky it becomes, refusing to eat 
foods it once did until it finds food that its never had before or is extremely high quality. Some even starve this way from stubbornness.

Male Oinkologne forgo their picky appetite and instead focus on their own beauty and complexion. If anything damages its pristinely 
glossy skin, it will enact unneccessary levels of violence towards them. While it can excrete aroma from its own tail, it often will bond 
with a female Oinkologne or another aroma-based Pokemon and guard them as if they were worth more than gold.

Tandemaus are never alone. If one is found alone without any other Tandemaus nearby, it will scream in excrutiating pain. Researchers

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
There is no difference between Tandemaus and Maushold from the basis of species. However if at least 4 Tandemaus group together, they’re 
clasified as a separate Pokemon with greater strength in a family unit. Tandemaus is one of the fastest breeders, with eggs that hatch within 
2 hours if the conditions are ideal. In the wild, Maushold can consist of nearly 80 Tandemaus, since to them, Family is Everything.

Weezing

============================================================
PAGE 669
============================================================
Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Galarian Weezing are practically mandatory for any modern day factory that is regulated efficiently. Toxic waste and poisonous gasses 
can be consumed by Galarian Weezing and converted into clean white smoke clouds. Much like normal Weezings it can also reverse 
the process, utilizing its toxin storage within battle to expunge poison at their enemies.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Wild Shroodle abhore fighting so they often mark their territory and nests with a poisonous liquid that has the same liquidity as paint. 
Most wild Pokemon are aware if they find these markings that they should stay away and avoid the native Shroodle habitat. If a Shroodle 
feels threatened it will sink its teeth into its enemy, injecting acid into them and causing temporary paralysis, immobilizing them.
Shroodle (Base) > Grafaiai (30)

Grafaiai keep the non-confrontational disposition of its previous form but instead gains a territorial ego based on the fear it derrives. It

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Using the minerals from the rock or fuel in its body it creates toxic fumes from its cylinders which can be overheated to even form 
flames! Similar to Rotom, many Trainers decide to tame a Revavroom and combine it with their vehicles to enhance its body and shape 
their vehicles into weapons. As of late, many Motorcycle gangs employ the usage of Revavroom to enhance their horsepower output.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Mr. Rime are often found on street corners simply tap dancing and creating ice sculptures to pass the time. Without training, they lose 
the desire to battle and instead engage in the smaller enjoyments of life. They also gain an icicle cane which they use to perform more 
tricks and keep their balance whenever they slip on their own ice stages. They lose some mobility as they evolve so yes it’s possible. 
Mime Jr. (Base) > Mr. Mime (20)
Mime Jr. (Base) > Galarian Mr. Mime (20) > Mr. Rime (35)

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
A key indicator in knowing you’re near a woobat’s habitat is if you find a mucus covered heart shape on the walls of a cave. Woobat 
uses its nose to subconciously stick to a high wall in the cave when it would sleep. While not fully developed, Woobat can emit 
ultrasonic waves that give it a general sense of its environment, however they still tend to wander aimlessly in caves. 
Woobat (Base) > Swoobat (20)

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Now developing eyes, Swoobat tend to not use sound waves for navigation but instead of mating, combat and communication. 
Swoobat are often captured and used within therapy, considering some sound waves have a soothing effect on people’s moods. Some 
cultures have twisting designs for their wedding rings due to the tails of Swoobat, who mate for life once they find a partner. 
Woobat (Base) > Swoobat (20)

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Despite its frilly appearance, Flittle has a harsh personality. As it flies around its habitat it will mark certain berry plants that it prefers and 
if other Pokemon steal from it, it’ll hold a grudge on them. Next time it finds someone it has a grudge on it will chase them down and 
exact their revenge. These methods of revenge are often cruel and unusual, despite being limited to its small size.

713
Flittle

============================================================
PAGE 714
============================================================
Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
When Flittle evolves into Espathra, it will systematically go through its list of grudges and exact each of them before doing anything 
else. Using its immense psychic powers it can sprint at vast speeds, reaching up to 120 mph if it’s angry enough. Its Psychic powers can 
also be used to flash bright lights at its enemies, often immobilizing or blinding their enemies from the intensity. 
Flittle (Base) > Espathra (30)

PAGE 747

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Glimmet are only found within very deep caverns where shards grow, which is its primary food source. The color of its petals is 
dependant on the shards it consumes. The petals themselves are not actual flowers but instead crystalized poison which is secreted and 
hardened from its bulbous body. From this body it also can scatter poisonous pollen that deters other Terravores from being near it. 
Glimmet (Base) > Glimmora (30)

PAGE 748

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
The visual appearance of Glimmora is highly determined by its diet and ratio of shard colors it consumed before evolving, leading to 
many unique floral patterns for collecotrs. Though usually coiled on the walls of caverns, whenever Glimmora feels threatened it will 
open up its petals and shoot out its petals to impale and poison anyone nearby. These petals usually take a week to regrow. 
Glimmet (Base) > Glimmora (30)

Height - 5’ 3” / 1.6m (Medium)

Diet - Herbivore
Slowpoke tend to only evolve when coming in contact with an Aethian Shellder. The shellders bite their tails due being mistaken for 
the tail the Aethian Variant. As a Slowbro ages however, the Shellder is slowly starved due to lack of poison to consume, then slowly 
petrifies. However it never releases its bite on the Slowbro. Researchers suggest Slowbro have a dulled sense of pain.
762

Diet - Herbivore
While it is rare for an Aethian Shellder to release its grip from a Slowbro, some do instead of dying from lack of nutrients. They tend to 
leave behind a carcass of stone when they do so. Some Slowpoke happen across these carcasses, known as King’s Rocks, and adorn it 
as a crown of regality. Once evolving to a Slowking they tend to gain intelligence from the pearl left behind.

When Staryu evolves, the shape of its shell expands and its core becomes more polished and refined, allowing it to grow another set of 
appendages which it can use to speed through the ocean like a propeller. The core is fairly expensive as a fashion accessory, however 
no researcher has figured out how utilize its core for any psionic based magitech, almost as if it has a mind of its own.

Swanna

============================================================
PAGE 809
============================================================
Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Basculin are known as the bullies of the sea. 99% of the time you find a Basculin it will be picking a fight with either a weaker Pokemon 
or someone stronger than it to prove a point. These fights are often only to display dominance and have little to do with any personal 
grudges. They are very commonly hated by the fishing community due to their ability to break fishing lines with their sharp teeth.
Basculin (Base) > Basculegion (30)
Species Starting Attacks
Aqua Jet, Water Gun, Tackle, Tail Whip

40 Flail - Normal
45 Waterfall - Water
50 Sky Uppercut - Fighting

============================================================
PAGE 810
============================================================
Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Due to the aggressive and competitive nature of Basculin, many are killed in the process of establishing a social hierarchy in an area of 
water. Every now and then a Basculegion will form as the spirit of the slain Basculin coalesce into one form. Basculegion are the pack 
leaders and alpha Pokemon, often leading other Basculin to fight off natural predators such as Gyarados or Huntail. 
Basculin (Base) > Basculegion (30)
Species Starting Attacks

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Before modern day vehicles were invented or even Rapidash were domesticated, Cyclizar were the primary method of transportation 
in the early ages. They have evolved over time and developed a mutualism nature with its allies, where it allows them to ride its back in 
exchange for the rider’s body heat. When it is heated this way it lifts the Cyclizar’s mood and becomes much more obedient. 
Cyclizar (Base)

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
This small fish pokemon is deceptively a dragon type, and one of the more intelligent ones. Tatsugiri is known as the false predator, 
as it clings to large water Pokemon and commands them to hunt for it while their bulky body protects it from harm. Even if tatsugiri is 
decently strong, it prefers saving its own energy while controlling its partner to gain even more food than it would on its own. 
Tatsugiri (Base)  
Species Starting Attacks
Water Gun, Dragon Breath, Splash, Helping Hand

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
The apron on the chest of Bombirdier is made of feathers that were shed from itself or its parents. This apron is sturdy enough to carry 
the weight of nearly anything. Bombirdier often collects rocks, food and other debris ithat interest it into its apron and either carries 
them back to its nest or uses them in combat to throw at their enemies. It’ll often drop rocks on its enemies just to piss them off.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Flamigo are masters at a technique known as “Synchronizing”. When in a flock with other Pokemon, it will synchronize its movements to 
exactly match its allies and attack as one. Some find this form of mimicry to be a form of attention seeking, as it usually enjoys being the 
center of attention. Flamigo tend to have large egos and if given praise, it will be easier to interact with.

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
The personality of Squawkabilly is heavily dependant on the color of its Plumage, being variants of green, yellow, blue or white. Green 
Variants are often noisy city dwellers. Yellow Variants are vicious, hotheaded and fierce. Blue Variants enjoy socializing and forming 
gangs with other avian Pokemon. White Variants are often social city dwellers, getting along the most with humans and merchants.

PAGE 900

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Klawf will frequently hang to the sides and undersides of cliffs and mountains, waiting for prey to pass by before lunging and 
tearing into them. Despite the blood rushing to their heads, they seem to be unaware to the health issues that may arise from being 
upsidedown too long. As a result, if a Klawf doesn’t find a victim within a few hours, they’ll be found upside-down and unconcious.

============================================================
PAGE 904
============================================================
Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Orthworm are normally passive creatures that live in deserts, consuming rocks for their iron deposits to sustain itself. If slighted, 
Orthworm will shape the tendrils of its body into fists, expanding them from the holes in its armor to pummel its opponents in combat. 
The body of Orthworm itself is blue and gooey in consistency and as they grow, they form a steel carapace with the iron it consumes. 
Orthworm (Base)

Slice, Mach Punch, Wrap, Harden

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
The excess bodyfat on Veluza tend to slow the bloodflow to its vital organs so it tends to shed and discard unneccessary flesh. 
Whenever it does so its reflexes get sharper, its fins become swifter and its mind becomes more honed, resulting in a large power 
increase which can easily be regenerated. The skin shed off Veluza is a common staple in seafood restaurants, though not a delicacy.

PAGE 926

Dex Entry
Base Stats
Evolution Path
Level-Up Attack List
Unlike normal Pokemon, Eevee are harder to evolve with pure experience. Eevee require a kinship to a pack of wild Pokemon it deems 
as family, or a connection to a Trainer, in order to evolve. Once it establishes a pack to bond with it will evolve based on the conditions 
of that pack. For Example, a Maelstrom Trainer would be able to evolve Vaporeon. Some Evolutions may be forced w/Elemental Stones.

Alolan Diglett are known to have small hair follicles that sprout from its head. These are often used as sensors that detect iron content 
within the ground. This helps it find roots of plants which it uses for nutrients that are highly rich in nutrients for it. While it prefers to eat 
minerals, it will often eat plants and vegetables for the sake of enjoyment, or for the sake of troubling local farmers. 
939
Alolan Diglett

============================================================
PAGE 940
============================================================
Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Once an Alolan Diglett has eaten enough minerals and Iron, its hair follicles will grow out to an entire wig. It becomes very prideful of 
this wig, often seeking out other digletts to form a trio of diglett, forming dugtrio. They serve as a clique more or less, boasting at other 
Pokemon and mocking their inferior looks. Its hair never moves unless they’re in a magnetic location, making it go frizzy.

Alolan Vulpix are fairly beloved due to its cute qualities, however are only found in nearly subzero regions. Due to its popular nature, 
it is common for Pokemon Hunters to take them from their habitats and breed them in captivity. As such, when a Vulpix is not in cold 
temperature, they become very frail and weak, losing all luster and sheen on their normally luxuriously silky fur.

Evolution Path
The toughest of Galarian Linoone will evolve into Obstagoon, serving as leaders of the pack that are charged with training the runts 
of the litter. Obstagoon never chases prey unlike its previous forms, however if prey runs into it, it will attempt to prevent them from 
escaping. After it traps prey, it yells very loudly, alerting nearby pack members to come to its location.

Galarian Farfetch’d (Base) > Sirfetch’d (25)
Compared to normal Farfetch’d, Galarian Farfetch’d prefer ground combat. It abandons the air entirely and the use of its wings as it 
prefers to use its Leak for combat. Pokemon Researchers state that Farfetch’d aren’t born with Leaks, though the Aethian variety quickly 
search for a Leak upon the first week of birth. They will run away if they don’t have one and conflict arises.

Evolution Path
Galarian Stunfisk can often be found in areas of high Iron content and little conductivity such as underground or in temples. They’re 
often brought in by Trainers that wish to protect an area to ensnare any wandering Pokemon or Treasure Hunters that may disturb an 
area. To defend an area, this Stunfisk hides under mud and snaps at the first target, rarely ever letting go without causing damage.

While it is commonly suggested that energy expended releases heat, it is the opposite for Galarian Darumaka. As they’re in a cold

Studies show that the heat sac within normal species of Darmanitan are inactive and cold most of the time. However whenever Darmanitan 
feels threatened or angered, it will turn into its Zen Form and erupt into flames. All stored energy will be converted into heat and power its 
heat sac. This process usually provides them with enough heat to last for 3 hours until they burn out from exhaustion.

A rather lazy Pokemon. Its diet mainly consists of plants that grow by the shores of beaches of ponds. After it eats it tends to take 
long naps by those areas, dipping its tail in the water. Unfortunately for this variant they stopped by polluted areas, having their tails 
poisoned in the process. Researchers suggest that Slowpoke is either unaware it’s poisoned or it just doesn’t care.

Hisuian Qwilfish

============================================================
PAGE 971
============================================================
Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Overqwil are only found within deep sea ravines with their qwills jabbed into stone walls. It waits until prey come near it, expands its 
spikes or shoots qwills at it to poison and kill it, only then will it resume resting and waiting on the stone walls. Even large sea Pokemon 
such as Kingdra and Gyarados steer clear of this monster as anyone who draws its spite will be ruthlessly attacked without mercy.
Hisuian Qwilfish (Base) > Overqwil (30)

Hisuian Voltorb

============================================================
PAGE 973
============================================================
Dex Entry
Base Stats
Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Unlike other phototrophs, Electrode cannot control the process of conversion from sunlight to energy. As such whenever it would 
become overcharged with electricity it becomes angry until it is able to discharge any residual electricity. Whenever this would occur it 
tends to hide in shaded areas to avoid sunlight, or roll into a barren area only to explode without anyone nearby being hurt. 
Hisuian Voltorb (Base) > Hisuian Electrode (30)

Dex Entry

Level-Up Attack List
Evolution Path
Compared to its normal variant, Hisuian Sneasel are lone hunters. To gain an edge in battle though this variant lives near marsh waters 
and dips its claws into the toxic waters, giving it a poisonous edge in battle. In order to prove themselves worthy to go without a pack, 
these Sneasel often ambush more inexperienced prey, taking any valuables they have with a threat to poison them otherwise. 
Hisuian Sneasel (Base) > Sneasler (35)

Evolution Path
As Sneasel evolves, its body adapts to the poison and their claws restructure around it so it doesn’t infect the rest of its body. As a result 
a high concentration of venom is located within its claws, leading to insanely venomous strikes even if its defeated. Sneaslers of this 
variant have proven their own competence without a pack and tend to be egotistical lone hunters that are disciplined and deadly.

When Clodsire is attacked, it will retaliate by sticking thick spines out of its body, though it often damages the internals of its body

Evolution Path
The flesh of a Toedscruel’s head is extremely delicious and highly sought after by chefs, however the natural rage of wild Toedscruel 
tend to make this task hard to accomplish. They often live deep within muggy forests in colonies and despise the presence of any other 
Pokemon or Trainer. When attacking its prey, it will wrap around them and jab its mouth into them, siphoning their nutrients until dry.

Kartana are the typical soldiers used by golemancers within the planet of Eden. Made from a special paper that is harvested from 
trees in specifically enchanted forests, their bodies are as hard as steel and able to cut through nearly any armor that can be crafted by 
humans. Kartana typically attack their enemies by swarming them in a group of 10 or so, inflicting death by a thousand cuts.
